  <bioghist id="bad7abe3eb7a5efbfb0c0b2c7f972487">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Linda Fingerson supported the Ford Foundation's grant administration activities for nearly twenty years. Her Ford career began in 1990 when she worked as an Administrative Assistant in the Program Division. She was promoted to a Senior Administrative Assistant in 2000 and then promoted again in 2003 to become a Grants Administrator. She stayed in that position for six years until she departed the foundation in 2009.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="a8b5ac9436e7569e81801e0548e37466">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>Collections holds the subject files of Ford Foundation staff member Linda Fingerson. The records were created during Fingerson's time as an Administrative Assistant in the Program Division.</p><p>
The collection consists of only one series. This series contains a group of subject files that Fingerson created to document her work supporting the administration of the Ford Foundation's Education, Media, Arts, and Culture Program (EMAC) and its Media, Arts, and Culture Unit (MAC) between 1996 and 1998.  </p>  </scopecontent>
